meanings.definition: Not able to be named or identified.
meanings.sent1: The mysterious creature in the forest was truly unnamable.
meanings.sent2: The feeling of fear she experienced was unnamable.
meanings.sent3: The unnamable shadow in the corner made everyone curious.
meanings.sent4: The unnamable beauty of the sunset left us speechless.
meanings.sent5: The unnamable scent of the flower filled the room with a sweet aroma.

meanings.sent1: The unnamable force behind the magic trick amazed the audience.
meanings.sent2: The unnamable power of the storm was frightening.
meanings.sent3: The unnamable taste of the new dish puzzled the chef.
meanings.sent4: The unnamable chaos of the city streets was overwhelming.
meanings.sent5: The unnamable sound of the wind in the night was eerie.
